1
00:01:24,439 --> 00:01:25,079
Lord Pan.

2
00:01:25,239 --> 00:01:26,040
Golden Guard Pan.

3
00:01:28,439 --> 00:01:29,640
General Ning has returned.

4
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:31,840
What is the meaning of this?

5
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:33,760
My lords, please don't panic.

6
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,359
I just received word

7
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:36,719
that bandits have entered the city.

8
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:38,239
And their target

9
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:40,680
is none other than you, my lords.

10
00:01:42,079 --> 00:01:42,519
Move!

11
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:44,319
Hurry!

12
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,519
My lords, please remain here.

13
00:01:46,879 --> 00:01:48,159
My men will protect you.

14
00:01:48,519 --> 00:01:49,760
You may rest assured.

15
00:01:50,519 --> 00:01:51,760
Once I've wiped out the bandits,

16
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:53,680
you, my lords, will be safe.

17
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:55,840
General Ning.

18
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,480
As Prefect of Lingzhou,

19
00:01:57,879 --> 00:01:58,719
with bandits causing chaos,

20
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,760
how could I hide away

21
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:01,480
and abandon the people?

22
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:04,120
Lord Zhang is truly a fine official.

23
00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:06,159
However,

24
00:02:06,519 --> 00:02:07,959
you lords are all civil officials.

25
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,199
Matters of swords and spears

26
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:13,120
should be left to us professionals.

27
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,280
General Ning has come from afar...

28
00:02:16,439 --> 00:02:16,919
Old Pan.

29
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:17,719
Here.

30
00:02:18,199 --> 00:02:19,240
I'm leaving this place to you.

31
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:20,919
Before I return,

32
00:02:21,719 --> 00:02:23,319
not even a fly may slip out.

33
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:25,479
Rest assured, General.

34
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:28,280
Not a single fly will get out.

35
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,039
Yes, sir!

36
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,280
He wants to put us under house arrest.

37
00:02:33,879 --> 00:02:35,400
Has he discovered something?

38
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,639
The Emperor's sword is here!

39
00:02:39,039 --> 00:02:41,240
Any who resist shall be killed on sight!

40
00:02:41,879 --> 00:02:42,439
Yes, sir!

41
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:47,560
Lord Zhang.

42
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,159
Have another drink.

43
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,080
Careful.

44
00:03:17,319 --> 00:03:18,039
How's it going, Old Gao?

45
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,400
Just as you instructed,

46
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:20,360
everything's arranged.

47
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:22,919
Why are you panting like that?

48
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,560
It's an uphill climb, you know.

49
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:28,280
Haven't been exercising lately?

50
00:03:28,719 --> 00:03:29,520
Why are you so out of shape?

51
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:29,960
You...

52
00:03:30,439 --> 00:03:31,319
You're the one out of shape.

53
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,840
Come on, let's go check it out.

54
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,639
The boss is inspecting.

55
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:44,960
Hey, guys,

56
00:03:45,439 --> 00:03:46,800
put down whatever you're doing.

57
00:03:47,159 --> 00:03:47,680
Take a break.

58
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:48,280
Come here.

59
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,280
Stop the cart, stop, stop.

60
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,759
Park it over there.

61
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:51,639
All right.

62
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:54,240
Yours truly

63
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:55,840
came here today

64
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,400
to pick out some lumber.

65
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,759
To take back

66
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,599
to reclaim land and plant a forest.

67
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,280
Who's the boss around here?

68
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,840
Who's in charge?

69
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:09,719
I'm the one in charge here.

70
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,919
They call me Big Tall Guy.

71
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:20,040
You're the one in charge?

72
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:20,680
What of it?

73
00:04:22,319 --> 00:04:22,959
Don't I look the part?

74
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,319
Judging by your clothes,

75
00:04:26,759 --> 00:04:27,920
you don't look like lumber buyers.

76
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:29,480
More like you're here to cause trouble.

77
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,199
If you don't get lost,

78
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:33,399
don't blame us for getting rough.

79
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,160
Inspectorate.

80
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:43,199
On official business.

81
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:44,959
Routine inspection.

82
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,519
Everyone behave yourselves!

83
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,800
My lords,

84
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,680
we're all villagers from Longevity Village.

85
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:53,399
We're chopping some lumber here

86
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:56,079
to build houses back home.

87
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:58,439
We're sorry for offending you earlier,

88
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,480
please forgive us.

89
00:05:03,079 --> 00:05:04,480
Longevity Village is

90
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:05,879
over ten li from here.

91
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,959
You came all this way for lumber

92
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,319
just to build houses?

93
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,319
That excuse you just gave,

94
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,759
do you even believe it yourself?

95
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:15,879
My lord,

96
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,560
the lumber here

97
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:18,879
is very old.

98
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,839
We use it for roof beams back home.

99
00:05:31,639 --> 00:05:33,160
Oh, I see.

100
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:36,920
This lumber does look

101
00:05:37,319 --> 00:05:38,800
quite fine indeed.

102
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,519
This... this...

103
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,519
Flint?

104
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,079
This is gold ore!

105
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:56,560
Hiding gold ore inside the wood,

106
00:05:56,759 --> 00:05:57,160
planning

107
00:05:57,639 --> 00:06:00,040
to throw it in the river and float it downstream.

108
00:06:00,639 --> 00:06:02,079
You may not be big,

109
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:03,839
but you're pretty smart.

110
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,079
Talk.

111
00:06:05,759 --> 00:06:06,639
Whose idea was this?

112
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,680
My lord,

113
00:06:08,439 --> 00:06:09,720
let me give you a word of advice.

114
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,759
You'd better mind your own business.

115
00:06:12,319 --> 00:06:13,879
Gold mines belong to the court.

116
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:16,759
Daring to mine them illegally

117
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,920
is a crime punishable by death for nine generations.

118
00:06:23,639 --> 00:06:25,759
Quite the official airs you've got.

119
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:35,120
Get out of the way.

120
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,600
So you're the kingpin around here?

121
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,240
Now we've caught you red-handed.

122
00:06:46,399 --> 00:06:48,120
Ready to surrender quietly?

123
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,319
The Emperor is far away.

124
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:57,399
In Longevity Village of Yang'an County,

125
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,800
I'm the one who calls the shots.

126
00:07:01,639 --> 00:07:02,480
In that case,

127
00:07:03,079 --> 00:07:04,959
don't blame my boys for getting rough.

128
00:07:05,319 --> 00:07:05,920
Kill them!

129
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:06,480
Get them!

130
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,160
Nobody move!

131
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:19,079
Fire!

132
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,079
Forgot to load the ammo.

133
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,439
What are you clicking for?

134
00:07:32,759 --> 00:07:33,360
Where's Old Feng?

135
00:07:33,879 --> 00:07:34,480
Who are you asking?

136
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:40,279
Old Feng!

137
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,079
Now he's singing too?

138
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:43,079
Get him!

139
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:49,839
Don't move!

140
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:50,680
Nobody move!

141
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:52,839
Stay put!

142
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:55,680
Get down!

143
00:07:57,399 --> 00:07:57,839
Don't move!

144
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,160
Listen up, all of you!

145
00:08:01,519 --> 00:08:02,720
Inspectorate, on official business.

146
00:08:03,959 --> 00:08:05,079
Anyone who resists

147
00:08:05,839 --> 00:08:07,120
will be killed on the spot.

148
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:08,959
Wha- wha- what...

149
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,000
What the hell is this thing?

150
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,720
The kind of thing that'll take your life.

151
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:15,839
Don't think these little tricks

152
00:08:15,959 --> 00:08:17,040
are gonna scare me.

153
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,279
A tough nut, aren't you?

154
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:22,480
Ning Chen.

155
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:23,639
Hand me the gun.

156
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:24,800
I'll blow a few holes in him.

157
00:08:24,959 --> 00:08:26,040
Let's see how much guts he has.

158
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:26,959
Who do you think you are,

159
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:28,360
messing with the Inspectorate?

160
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,759
Now's your moment to shine.

161
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,320
Make up for your mistakes.

162
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,000
So you're Ning Chen.

163
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,600
So you've heard of me.

164
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,879
Weren't you so tough just now?

165
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,919
Think I wouldn't dare kill you?

166
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:49,080
Your crime is punishable by death for nine generations.

167
00:08:49,799 --> 00:08:52,679
Don't think you'll slip through the joint trial.

168
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:53,879
Let me tell you something.

169
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:56,000
If you piss me off,

170
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,679
I'll finish you in a heartbeat...

171
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,320
You'd better let me go.

172
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,840
You have no idea who you're crossing

173
00:09:05,159 --> 00:09:07,240
by arresting me.

174
00:09:07,399 --> 00:09:08,240
A big shot?

175
00:09:10,399 --> 00:09:11,480
Bigger than the Emperor's brother-in-law?

176
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,679
I even dared to behead him.

177
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,320
What kind of big shot

178
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:19,080
could a tiny place like Lingzhou produce?

179
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,159
Besides,

180
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,600
even if Lingzhou had such a big shot,

181
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,399
could he protect a petty bandit like you?

182
00:09:28,679 --> 00:09:30,960
Worst case, I do a few years in prison.

183
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:33,360
When I get out, I'll still be a tough guy.

184
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,639
That actually rhymes.

185
00:09:36,759 --> 00:09:38,320
Didn't know we had a rapper here.

186
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:39,720
But you really can't seem to tell

187
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,960
who's really in charge here.

188
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,799
Your life is in my hands now.

189
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:44,919
Understand?

190
00:09:48,559 --> 00:09:49,480
A rapper? What's that mean?

191
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:52,559
Exactly what it sounds like.

192
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:55,679
A rapper.

193
00:09:56,759 --> 00:09:57,200
Come here.

194
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:58,720
Think about it.

195
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:00,720
I beheaded the Emperor's brother-in-law.

196
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:02,200
And His Majesty said nothing, right?

197
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,360
Nothing at all.

198
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,200
So I beheaded the imperial uncle,

199
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,519
and His Majesty didn't say a word.

200
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,960
So what do you think

201
00:10:09,159 --> 00:10:11,320
my relationship with His Majesty is?

202
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,600
What could it be?

203
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:17,519
Could it be...

204
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:19,320
you're his illegitimate son?

205
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,559
How could you blurt that out?

206
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:22,879
Do you even have a brain?

207
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,360
Tell you what.

208
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,360
Everything you know,

209
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,080
spill it all to me, every detail.

210
00:10:32,159 --> 00:10:33,440
I'll pull strings through my father

211
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,759
and spare your life. How's that?

212
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:35,799
Really?

213
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:39,600
I'll talk.

214
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,360
I'll talk, I'll talk, I'll talk.

215
00:10:43,279 --> 00:10:45,399
It's Zhang Yuancang, Prefect of Lingzhou.

216
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,279
I was just a local drifter,

217
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,440
and he took me under his wing

218
00:10:49,759 --> 00:10:51,519
to do his shady dirty work.

219
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,639
Running gambling dens, running brothels,

220
00:10:53,759 --> 00:10:54,759
and digging up gold mines here.

221
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,039
What a despicable scumbag.

222
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,320
A truly corrupt dog of an official.

223
00:10:57,639 --> 00:10:58,159
Corrupt dog.

224
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,799
Now I want to know,

225
00:11:01,519 --> 00:11:02,120
this gold,

226
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,960
does it end up in Zhang Yuancang's hands,

227
00:11:04,559 --> 00:11:06,399
or is it shipped off somewhere else?

228
00:11:08,519 --> 00:11:10,320
Once, when Lord Zhang got drunk,

229
00:11:11,159 --> 00:11:12,240
that corrupt dog had too much to drink,

230
00:11:12,679 --> 00:11:13,320
and I heard him say

231
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:16,879
that once the ore is refined into gold,

232
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,720
it's secretly sent to the capital.

233
00:11:19,799 --> 00:11:20,919
Sent to the capital.

234
00:11:22,799 --> 00:11:24,840
He discovered a gold mine and dared to mine it privately?

235
00:11:25,039 --> 00:11:26,240
This man has some serious nerve.

236
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:27,759
Perhaps

237
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:29,080
and probably holds a high position too.

238
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:32,000
No wonder every memorial Jiang Zhengyang submitted

239
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:34,279
sank without a trace.

240
00:11:34,919 --> 00:11:35,679
Perhaps

241
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,399
they have someone backing them higher up.

242
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:38,799
Hold on a moment.

243
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,799
For a memorial to reach the throne,

244
00:11:41,919 --> 00:11:43,200
it must first be reviewed by the Cabinet.

245
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:46,159
Could the man behind this be so powerful

246
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:47,559
that he can reach into the Cabinet?

247
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,080
Who could possibly pull that off?

248
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,200
Not many.

249
00:11:52,159 --> 00:11:52,919
Eunuch Quan.

250
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:53,879
The Left Chancellor.

251
00:11:54,039 --> 00:11:54,600
The Right Chancellor.

252
00:11:54,879 --> 00:11:56,080
And the princes in the palace.

253
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,320
Your Highness Ning,

254
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,399
I've told you everything I know.

255
00:12:04,759 --> 00:12:06,200
You must keep your promise.

256
00:12:08,159 --> 00:12:11,320
What promise?

257
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,679
Wait, your father, isn't he...

258
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,679
Don't spread rumors.

259
00:12:17,039 --> 00:12:17,720
I get it.

260
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,559
My lips are sealed.

261
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:20,559
No way.

262
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,639
This guy knows too many secrets.

263
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,679
He's clearly got a loose tongue. Kill him.

264
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:25,120
Your Highness!

265
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:26,840
I know one more secret.

266
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,600
Can it buy me my life?

267
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,600
See? I knew he had a loose tongue.

268
00:12:30,759 --> 00:12:31,200
Exactly.

269
00:12:31,399 --> 00:12:31,960
Exactly.

270
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:32,799
Well, go on then.

271
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,279
Let me see if this secret

272
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,159
is worth sparing your sorry life.

273
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:39,360
Your Highness,

274
00:12:44,399 --> 00:12:46,399
your mother, the Consort, was murdered.

275
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:53,879
What?
